The paper discusses resource allocation in wireless communication systems, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several CS sub-disciplines. However, based on the content of the paper, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), as the paper deals with optimization problems related to wireless resource allocation. The use of machine learning also suggests that the paper could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning), while the involvement of cloud computing could place it under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of historical data and offline optimization, which could be relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), respectively.
